22/12/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The interior ministry on Sunday (December 21st) charged three people in connection with a deadly attack on a police patrol last month. Suspects Rexhal Kasami, Ramadani Sakiri and Agim Islami face charges of murder and attempted murder. Police arrested them on Saturday, along with 17 other people allegedly involved in the attack. Gunmen firing from a vehicle killed one police officer and injured two others near the Faculty of Science and Mathematics in northern Skopje on November 26th. (MIA, Makfax, A1, MINA - 21/12/08)
